Asplenium ruta-muraria.label: Asplenium ruta-muraria
Asplenium ruta-muraria.description: Asplenium ruta-muraria is a species of fern commonly known as wall-rue. In Germany, it is known as Mauerraute or Mauerstreifenfarn. It is a very small epipetric species, growing exclusively on limestone and other calcareous rocks. Wikipedia

Botrychium lunaria.label: Botrychium lunaria
Botrychium lunaria.description: Botrychium lunaria is a species of fern known by the common name common moonwort. It is the most widely distributed moonwort, growing throughout the Northern Hemisphere across Eurasia and from Alaska ... Wikipedia

Calamites.label: Calamites
Calamites.description: Calamites is a genus of extinct arborescent horsetails to which the modern horsetails are closely related. Unlike their herbaceous modern cousins, these plants were medium-sized trees, growing to heights of more than 30 meters. Wikipedia

Cryptogramma crispa.label: Cryptogramma crispa
Cryptogramma crispa.description: Cryptogramma crispa, the parsley fern, is a species of Arctic–alpine fern. It produces separate sterile and fertile fronds, up to 30 cm tall, and is a pioneer species on acidic screes. Wikipedia

Cystopteris fragilis.label: Cystopteris fragilis
Cystopteris fragilis.description: Cystopteris fragilis is a species of fern known by the common names brittle bladderfern and common fragile fern. It can be found worldwide, generally in shady, moist areas. Wikipedia

Cyatheaceae.label: Cyatheaceae
Cyatheaceae.description: The Cyatheaceae are the scaly tree fern family and include the world's tallest tree ferns, which reach heights up to 20 m. Wikipedia

Diplazium esculentum.label: Diplazium esculentum
Diplazium esculentum.description: Vegetable fern is an edible fern found throughout Asia and Oceania. It is probably the most commonly consumed fern. The young fronds are stir-fried as a "vegetable" or used in salads. Wikipedia

Equisetaceae.label: Equisetaceae
Equisetaceae.description: Equisetaceae, sometimes called the horsetail family, is the only extant family of the order Equisetales, with one surviving genus, Equisetum, which comprises about twenty species. Wikipedia

Matteuccia struthiopteris.label: Ostrich Fern
Matteuccia struthiopteris.description: Matteuccia struthiopteris is a crown-forming, colony-forming fern, occurring in temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere in eastern and northern Europe, northern Asia and northern North America. Wikipedia

Nephrolepis exaltata.label: Nephrolepis exaltata
Nephrolepis exaltata.description: The Sword Fern is a species of fern in the family Lomariopsidaceae, native to tropical regions throughout the world. Wikipedia

Ophioglossales.label: Ophioglossales
Ophioglossales.description: Ophioglossales are a small group of pteridophyte plants. Traditionally they are included in the division Pteridophyta, the ferns, originally as a family and later as the order Ophioglossales. Wikipedia

Pilularia.label: Pilularia
Pilularia.description: Pilularia or pillworts is a genus of unusual ferns of family Marsileaceae distributed in North Temperate regions, Ethiopian mountains, and the southern hemisphere in Australia, New Zealand, and western South America. Wikipedia

Polypodium vulgare.label: Polypodium vulgare
Polypodium vulgare.description: Polypodium vulgare, the common polypody, is a fern of the Polypodiaceae family. Wikipedia

Polystichum aculeatum.label: Polystichum aculeatum
Polystichum aculeatum.description: Polystichum aculeatum is an evergreen fern native to Europe. It is most abundant in upland regions of the British Isles and western France, where it benefits from the combination of mild winters and ... Wikipedia

Polystichum lonchitis.label: Polystichum lonchitis
Polystichum lonchitis.description: Polystichum lonchitis is a species of fern known by the common name northern holly fern, or simply holly fern. It is native to much of the Northern Hemisphere from Eurasia to Alaska to Greenland and south into mountainous central North America. Wikipedia

Psilotum nudum.label: Psilotum nudum
Psilotum nudum.description: Psilotum nudum is a fernlike plant. Like the other species in the order Psilotales, it lacks roots. It is found in tropical Africa, Central America, tropical and subtropical North America, South America, ... Wikipedia

Salvinia natans.label: Salvinia natans
Salvinia natans.description: Salvinia natans is an annual floating aquatic fern, which can appear superficially similar to moss. It is found throughout the world where there is plentiful standing fresh water, sunlight, and humid ... Wikipedia

Sceptridium multifidum.label: Sceptridium multifidum
Sceptridium multifidum.description: Sceptridium multifidum is a fern species in the Ophioglossaceae, known by the common names leathery grapefern and leathery moonwort. Wikipedia

Anogramma.label: Anogramma
Anogramma.description:
Anogramma is a genus of ferns in the Pteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae. It contains about ten species, including
Anogramma ascensionis Diels 1899 – endemic to Ascension Island, South Atlantic ... Wikipedia

Asplenium.label: Asplenium
Asplenium.description: Asplenium is a genus of about 700 species of ferns, often treated as the only genus in the family Aspleniaceae, though other authors consider Hymenasplenium separate, based on molecular phylogenetic ... Wikipedia

Botrychium.label: Moonwort
Botrychium.description: Moonworts are ferns, seedless vascular plants, of the genus Botrychium, sensu stricto. They are small, with fleshy roots, and reproduce by spores shed into the air. Wikipedia

Cheilanthes.label: Cheilanthes
Cheilanthes.description: Cheilanthes is a genus of about 180 species of rock-dwelling ferns with a cosmopolitan distribution in warm, dry, rocky regions, often growing in small crevices high up on cliffs. Most are small, sturdy and evergreen. Wikipedia

Cystopteris.label: Cystopteris
Cystopteris.description: Cystopteris is a genus of ferns in the family Cystopteridaceae. These are known generally as bladderferns or fragile ferns. They are found in temperate areas worldwide. Wikipedia

Dicksonia.label: Dicksonia
Dicksonia.description: Dicksonia is a genus of tree ferns in the order Cyatheales. It is regarded as related to Cyathea, but is considered more primitive, dating back at least to the Jurassic and Cretaceous periods. The fossil record includes stems, pinnules, and spores. Wikipedia

Dryopteris.label: Dryopteris
Dryopteris.description: Dryopteris, commonly called wood fern, male fern, or buckler fern, is a genus of about 250 species of ferns with distribution in the temperate Northern Hemisphere, with the highest species diversity in eastern Asia. Wikipedia

Equisetum.label: Equisetum
Equisetum.description: Equisetum is the only living genus in Equisetaceae, a family of vascular plants that reproduce by spores rather than seeds. Wikipedia

Marsileaceae.label: Marsileaceae
Marsileaceae.description: The Marsileaceae are a small family of heterosporous aquatic and semi-aquatic ferns, though at first sight they do not physically resemble other ferns. Wikipedia

Osmundaceae.label: Osmundaceae
Osmundaceae.description: The Osmundaceae is a family of four genera and 15-25 species. It is the only fern family of the order Osmundales an order in the class Polypodiopsida or in some classifications the only order in the class Osmundopsida. Wikipedia

Salviniales.label: Salviniales
Salviniales.description: The order Salviniales is an order of ferns in the class Polypodiopsida. Salviniales are all aquatic and differ from all other ferns in being heterosporous, meaning that they produce two different types ... Wikipedia

Pteridium aquilinum.label: Pteridium aquilinum
Pteridium aquilinum.description: Pteridium aquilinum, also known as "eagle fern," is a species of fern occurring in temperate and subtropical regions in both hemispheres. The extreme lightness of its spores has led to its global distribution. Wikipedia

Thelypteridaceae.label: Thelypteridaceae
Thelypteridaceae.description:
Thelypteridaceae is a family of about 900 species of ferns in the eupolypods II clade of the order Polypodiales, in the class Polypodiopsida.
The ferns are terrestrial, with the exception of a few which are lithophytes. Wikipedia

Woodsiaceae.label: Woodsiaceae
Woodsiaceae.description: The Woodsiaceae or Cliff Ferns is a family of ferns in the Eupolypods II clade of the order Polypodiales, in the class Polypodiopsida. It contains the three genera Cheilanthopsis, Hymenocystis, and Woodsia. Wikipedia

Asplenium platyneuron.label: Asplenium platyneuron
Asplenium platyneuron.description: Asplenium platyneuron, commonly known as ebony spleenwort or brownstem spleenwort, is a fern native to North America east of the Rocky Mountains and to South Africa. Wikipedia

Microsorum pteropus.label: Microsorum pteropus
Microsorum pteropus.description: Microsorum pteropus, commonly known as Java fern, an aquatic fern from southeast Asia, is highly variable with several different geographic varieties that vary in leaf size and shape. It is found attached to roots and rocks in nature. Wikipedia

Marattiaceae.label: Marattiaceae
Marattiaceae.description: Class Marattiopsida is a group of ferns containing a single order, Marattiales, and family, Marattiaceae. Wikipedia

Osmunda japonica.label: Osmunda japonica
Osmunda japonica.description:
Osmunda japonica is a fern in the genus Osmunda native to eastern Asia, including Japan, China, Korea, Taiwan, and the far east of Russia on Sakhalin.
It is a deciduous herbaceous plant which produces separate fertile and sterile fronds. Wikipedia

Pecopteris.label: Pecopteris
Pecopteris.description: Pecopteris was a form genus of leaves from several unrelated plant groups that flourished the early Carboniferous period and on to c. 250 Ma. Wikipedia

Pteridales.label: Pteridales
Pteridales.description:
The Pteridales are ferns that have their sori in linear strips under the edge of the leaf tissue, usually with the edge of the lamina reflexed over.
This order is considered a family under the Smith classification. Wikipedia

Saccoloma.label: Saccoloma
Saccoloma.description: Saccoloma is a fern genus in family Saccolomataceae. It is pantropical and its species are found in wet, shaded forest areas. Saccoloma species are characterized by an omega-shaped vascular bundle in the cross-sections of their petioles. Wikipedia

Sceptridium.label: Sceptridium
Sceptridium.description: Sceptridium is a genus of seedless vascular plants, closely allied to the genus Botrychium. It is also closely related to the genus Botrypus. Sceptridium species are commonly called the grape-ferns. Wikipedia

Blechnum penna-marina.label: Blechnum penna-marina
Blechnum penna-marina.description: Blechnum penna-marina, alpine water fern or pinque, is a species of fern in the family Blechnaceae, with a natural range from the Araucanía Region to the south and from the coast to the tree line of ... Wikipedia

Pleopeltis polypodioides.label: Pleopeltis polypodioides
Pleopeltis polypodioides.description: Pleopeltis polypodioides is a species of creeping, coarse-textured fern native to the Americas and Africa. Wikipedia

Adiantum jordanii.label: Adiantum jordanii
Adiantum jordanii.description:
Adiantum jordanii is a perennial species of maidenhair fern, in the Vittarioideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae. The species is known by the common name California maidenhair.
It is native to California and Baja California. Wikipedia

Anogramma leptophylla.label: Anogramma leptophylla
Anogramma leptophylla.description: Anogramma leptophylla is a species of fern in the Pteridaceae family. It is found worldwide in temperate and subtropical regions. A rarity in the Pteridophyta, it is a fern whose sporophyte tends to have an annual life cycle. Wikipedia

Antrophyum austroqueenslandicum.label: Antrophyum austroqueenslandicum
Antrophyum austroqueenslandicum.description: Antrophyum austroqueenslandicum was a species of epiphytic or lithophytic fern known from subtropical rainforest in Lamington National Park in the state of Queensland, Australia. Wikipedia

Argyrochosma.label: Argyrochosma
Argyrochosma.description: Argyrochosma is a genus of ferns known commonly as false cloak ferns. The genus is included in the Cheilanthoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae. Wikipedia

Aspidotis californica.label: Aspidotis californica
Aspidotis californica.description:
Aspidotis californica is a species of fern known by the common name California lacefern. It is native to California and Baja California.
It grows in rock cracks and crevices in many types of habitat. Wikipedia

Asplenium serratum.label: Asplenium serratum
Asplenium serratum.description: Asplenium serratum, the Bird's nest spleenwort and Wild birdnest fern, is a fern native to Brazil, the Caribbean, and the United States. It is rare in central and southern Florida, where it is a state-listed endangered species. Wikipedia

Blechnum brasiliense.label: Blechnum brasiliense
Blechnum brasiliense.description:
Blechnum brasiliense is a fern in the genus Blechnum that is native to South America.
This is one of the better known and more common species of Blechnum in warmer climates. It forms a small trunk. Wikipedia

Ceratopteris thalictroides.label: Ceratopteris thalictroides
Ceratopteris thalictroides.description: The species Ceratopteris thalictroides is a fern species belonging to the genus Ceratopteris, one of only two genera of the Ceratopteridoideae subfamily of the family Pteridaceae. Wikipedia

Cyathea balanocarpa.label: Cyathea balanocarpa
Cyathea balanocarpa.description: Cyathea balanocarpa is a species of tree fern native to Cuba, Jamaica and Hispaniola. Despite its wide distribution, little is known about this species. It is apparently of hybrid origin. Wikipedia

Cyathea corcovadensis.label: Cyathea corcovadensis
Cyathea corcovadensis.description: Cyathea corcovadensis is a species of tree fern native to Paraguay and Serra do Mar in southern Brazil, where it grows in primary and secondary forest, as well as scrub, at an altitude of 250-2100 m. Wikipedia

Cyathea dregei.label: Cyathea dregei
Cyathea dregei.description: Cyathea dregei, also known as the Common Tree Fern and Gewone Boomvaring in Afrikaans, is a widespread species of tree fern in southern Africa. Wikipedia

Cyathea exilis.label: Cyathea exilis
Cyathea exilis.description: Cyathea exilis is a species of tree fern endemic to the Cape York Peninsula in Queensland, Australia, where it grows in vine forest on a substrate of sandstone. Wikipedia

Cyathea edanoi.label: Cyathea edanoi
Cyathea edanoi.description: Cyathea edanoi is a species of tree fern endemic to Luzon in the Philippines, where it grows in montane forest at an altitude of about 1300 m. The trunk is erect and 1–2 m tall. Fronds are bi- or tripinnate and approximately 1 m long. Wikipedia

Cyathea glabra.label: Cyathea glabra
Cyathea glabra.description: Cyathea glabra is a species of tree fern native to Borneo, western Java, Sumatra and the Malay Peninsula, where it grows in lowland swamp forest and montane forest at an elevation of up to 1500 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and 2-4 m tall. Wikipedia

Cyathea glauca.label: Cyathea glauca
Cyathea glauca.description:
Cyathea glauca is a species of tree fern endemic to Réunion. Little is known about this species.
C. glauca is not to be confused with Cyathea glauca used as a synonym of Cyathea mexicana. Wikipedia

Cyathea incana.label: Cyathea incana
Cyathea incana.description: Cyathea incana is a species of tree fern native to Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Bolivia, and northern Argentina. Very little is known about this plant. Wikipedia

Cyathea hornei.label: Cyathea hornei
Cyathea hornei.description: Cyathea hornei is a species of tree fern. Its natural distribution covers eastern New Guinea and the Louisiade Archipelago to Fiji, where it grows in wet submontane forest, stunted forest, mossy forest, and on ridges, at an altitude of 400-2000 m. Wikipedia

Lomariopsis.label: Lomariopsis
Lomariopsis.description:
Lomariopsis is the type genus of the family Lomariopsidaceae of the ferns.
One economically important species exists only as an aquatic gametophyte form, commonly known as süsswassertang. Wikipedia

Phegopteris hexagonoptera.label: Phegopteris hexagonoptera
Phegopteris hexagonoptera.description: Phegopteris hexagonoptera, commonly called the broad beech fern, is a common forest fern in the eastern United States and adjacent Ontario. It grows from a creeping rootstock, sending up individual fronds that more or less clump. Wikipedia

Psilotum complanatum.label: Psilotum complanatum
Psilotum complanatum.description: Psilotum complanatum is a rare herbaceous epiphytic fern ally in the genus Psilotum. There is some evidence that it might be a true fern that has lost some typically fern-like characteristics. Wikipedia

Ptisana salicina.label: Ptisana salicina
Ptisana salicina.description: Ptisana salicina, or king fern, is a species of fern native to Australia and the South Pacific. Large and robust with a distinctive tropical appearance, it has fronds up to 5 metres tall that arise from ... Wikipedia

Todea.label: Todea
Todea.description: The fern genus Todea is known from only two living species. Todea barbara L., known as the king fern, is native to South Africa, New Zealand, and Australia while Todea papuana H. is known only from Papua New Guinea. Wikipedia

Woodwardia areolata.label: Woodwardia areolata
Woodwardia areolata.description: Woodwardia areolata is a species of fern native to eastern North America. It is usually treated in the genus Woodwardia, in the eupolypods II clade of the order Polypodiales, in the class Polypodiopsida. Wikipedia

Asplenium × ebenoides.label: Asplenium × ebenoides
Asplenium × ebenoides.description: Asplenium × ebenoides is a hybrid fern native to eastern North America, part of the "Appalachian Asplenium complex" of related hybrids. Wikipedia

Asplenium anceps.label: Asplenium anceps
Asplenium anceps.description: Asplenium anceps is a diploid fern of Aspleniaceae family and one of the ancestors of the ferns that form the trichomanes complex. Wikipedia

Asplenium pinnatifidum.label: Asplenium pinnatifidum
Asplenium pinnatifidum.description: Asplenium pinnatifidum, commonly known as the lobed spleenwort or pinnatifid spleenwort, is a small fern found principally in the Appalachian Mountains and the Shawnee Hills, growing in rock crevices in moderately acid to subacid strata. Wikipedia

Niphidium crassifolium.label: Niphidium crassifolium
Niphidium crassifolium.description: Niphidium crassifolium commonly known as the graceful fern is a species of fern in the Polypodiaceae family found in Central and South America. Wikipedia

Athyrium angustum.label: Athyrium angustum
Athyrium angustum.description: Athyrium angustum is known as the northern lady fern, native to northeastern North America. It was long included in the superspecies Athyrium filix-femina, but is now largely recognized as a distinct species. Wikipedia

Bolbitis heteroclita.label: Bolbitis heteroclita
Bolbitis heteroclita.description: Bolbitis heteroclita is an aquatic fern species of Bolbitis, native to the Indochina region of tropical Southeast Asia. Wikipedia

Ceratopteris richardii.label: Ceratopteris richardii
Ceratopteris richardii.description: Ceratopteris richardii is a fern species belonging to the genus Ceratopteris, one of only two genera of the Ceratopteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae. It is one of several genera of ferns adapted to an aquatic existence. Wikipedia

Cheilanthes villosa.label: Cheilanthes villosa
Cheilanthes villosa.description: Cheilanthes villosa is a species of lip fern, whose common name is villous lipfern. This plant is native to the southwestern United States where it grows in rocky mountains and deserts. Wikipedia

Cryptogrammaceae.label: Cryptogrammaceae
Cryptogrammaceae.description: Cryptogrammaceae is a small family of ferns, which appears to be somewhat isolated from the rest of the Pteridales. This family forms a natural clade that is the most basal to the order. Of these, Llavea is the most basal within the clade. Wikipedia

Ctenitis.label: Ctenitis
Ctenitis.description: Ctenitis is a genus of large ferns in the Dryopteridaceae. Wikipedia

Llavea.label: Llavea cordifolia
Llavea.description: Llavea cordifolia is a fern, the sole species of its genus. It is often cultivated as an ornamental foliage plant. The genus was named in honour of Pablo de La Llave, a Mexican naturalist. Wikipedia

Notholaena californica.label: Notholaena californica
Notholaena californica.description: Notholaena californica is a species of fern known by the common name California cloak fern. It is native to southern California, Arizona, and adjacent northwestern Mexico, where it grows in dry and ... Wikipedia

Mohria.label: Mohria
Mohria.description: The fern genus Mohria is a small one of eight species, restricted to southern Africa and Madagascar. Plants in this genus superficially resemble Cheilanthes, but the sporangial structure indicates their close affinity to Anemia. Wikipedia

Athyrium filix-femina.label: Athyrium filix-femina
Athyrium filix-femina.description: Athyrium filix-femina is a large, feathery species of fern native throughout most of the temperate Northern Hemisphere, where it is often abundant in damp, shady woodland environments and is often grown for decoration. Wikipedia

Asplenium trichomanes.label: Asplenium trichomanes
Asplenium trichomanes.description: Asplenium trichomanes is a small fern in the spleenwort genus Asplenium. It is a widespread and common species, occurring almost worldwide in a variety of rocky habitats. It is a variable fern with several subspecies. Wikipedia
